gw.plugin.vendormanagement

Interface InvoiceAutomaticStateTransitionHelper


  • public interface InvoiceAutomaticStateTransitionHelper
    Describes how a helper should look, including methods to identify relevant invoices and process them.

      • getRelevantInvoices

        java.util.List<ServiceRequestInvoice> getRelevantInvoices(java.util.List<ServiceRequestInvoice> invoices)
        Retrieves all invoices in the supplied collection that are relevant to the current operation. Use this to filter the invoices based on prerequisites.
        Parameters:
        invoices - A collection of invoices.
        Returns:
        A list of the invoices to process.

      • qualify

        InvoiceAutomaticProcessingQualificationCheckResult qualify(ServiceRequestInvoice invoice)
        Check to see whether the supplied invoice qualifies for the action this class represents. The result object contains a success flag and a list of zero or more user-readable reasons why the invoice did not qualify.
        Returns:
        An QualificationCheckResult that summarizes the result of this test.

      • performAction

        void performAction(ServiceRequestInvoice invoice,
                   InvoiceAutomaticProcessingQualificationCheckResult checkResult)
        Apply the action represented by this class to the supplied invoice. This should only be called if getFailedToQualifyReasons(gw.api.validation.ValidationExecutionResult[]) succeeded, in which case we expect this to succeed. Any exceptions (including Validation errors) should be handled by the caller.
        Parameters:
        invoice - The invoice.
        checkResult - A summary of the results of the qualification step.

      • registerFailure

        void registerFailure(ServiceRequestInvoice invoice,
                     InvoiceAutomaticProcessingQualificationCheckResult checkResult)
        Records the fact that this invoice failed to qualify for the action represented by this class.

      • getFailedToQualifyMessage

        java.lang.String getFailedToQualifyMessage(java.util.List<java.lang.String> reasons)
        Converts the supplied list of reasons into a message suitable for display to the end user. For instance an implementation might use a displaykey like "The operation failed because: {0}" and pass in the joined list.
        Parameters:
        reasons - The reasons the operation failed.
        Returns:
        A user-friendly message based on those reasons.
